I've been to my share of Dunkin' locations, having lived in the US all my life, and this one was the worst. Train stations, airports, none hold a candle to this. I mean, I expected as much from a city spot, but still. This exceeded expectations in a bad way. Here's how my order went.  Me: "Hi, can I have X sandwich?" Cashier: "Oh we don't have that sandwich". Me: "Okay, that's fine. Do you have Y sandwich?" Cashier: *doesn't answer, types in Y sandwich, so I assume they have it* Me: "Can I also get Z sandwich?" Cashier: "Sure, mmhmm." Me: "Can I get a frozen lemonade?" Cashier: "Our machine is broken." Me: "Okay..." Getting frustrated at this point. "Can I have a regular lemonade?" Cashier: "We have tea lemonade." Me: "No, I mean like a regular lemonade. Not frozen. No tea." Cashier: "We have tea with lemonade." Me: *Marbles are now not only being lost, but are melting, brain is becoming liquified* "I don't want tea. I want just regular lemonade." Cashier: "Oh, I meant we only have tea WITH lemon." Me: "Okay fine, I'll take a tea with lemon."  Fast forward to when I've gotten my order, the man who took my order gave me two of the same sandwich instead of two different ones, and he also gave me... Wait for it... Tea. WITH LEMONADE. Not just lemons. LemonADE. Why was it impossible to get a straight lemonade but he then gave me something I didn't ask for that was made with an ingredient I actually wanted???

It's either a long line, a long wait, or something is made wrong. Thurs was it for me. It's not worth it.

I don't even want to give stars but apparently I have to. I literally just tried to go in and get breakfast and the staff didn't show up until 7:02 even though the sign clearly states that they open at 7. I wasn't aware that meant the staff shows up at 7 and they don't open until 730, and yes that is sarcasm. I do not usually write reviews however the fact that only one of the 3 girls even spoke to me whereas the other 2 just told her to close the door and didn't even want to answer me. Are the owners aware of their posted business hours and what time their staff is actually showing up? I have worked in a donut shop before and I know that if we opened at 5am I had to be there well before 5am. Either change your hours or change your staff, do something though because you have lost a customer that was about to buy breakfast for 3 other people besides myself and I really do not wish you success in your business if this is how you run your business. Good luck figuring it out...horrible.
